	<div class="blog-archive-entries-wrapper">
		<div id="unique-entry-id-247" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Bath Festival of Children's Literature</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Monday, 28 September 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-books.php">Books</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/" rel="external" title="www.vampirates.co.uk"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></a></div>The <a href="http://www.bathkidslitfest.co.uk/default.php" rel="external" title="http://www.bathkidslitfest.co.uk/default.php">Bath Festival of Children's Literature</a> would have finished today.  I hope everyone who went enjoyed themselves.  It sounded like a brilliant festival with several good books and authors listed including Jeremy Strong and Terry Deary (Horrible Histories).  Syren (Septimus Heap book 5) by Angie Sage was also listed, it is out in the UK as far as I can tell, but due out in Canada (and probably America) on 29th September.  Dreadnought (H.I.V.E book 4) by Mark Walden thankfully was also listed, I had not realised it had been released in the UK as here they don't seem to have heard of book 3!  (Time to talk really nicely to my Mother-in-Law).<br /><br />Don't forget you can still see Justin Somper at the <a href="http://appledorebookfestival.co.uk/authorsandtickets.htm" rel="external" title="http://appledorebookfestival.co.uk/authorsandtickets.htm">Appledore Book Festival</a>, on Thursday 1st October 2009, from 7.00pm he will be at St. Mary&rsquo;s Primary School (&pound;3) and the <a href="http://cheltenhamfestivals.com/literature/" rel="external" title="http://cheltenhamfestivals.com/literature/">Cheltenham Festival of Literature</a>, on Saturday 17th October 2009 with Maggie Stiefvater.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-246" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Busy week</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 26 September 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/" rel="external" title="www.vampirates.co.uk"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></a></div>Today (Saturday 26th September) from 5.00 to 5.45pm at Bath Central Library, Justin Somper will be doing his Vampirates show (&pound;4.50) as part of the <a href="http://www.bathkidslitfest.co.uk/default.php" rel="external" title="http://www.bathkidslitfest.co.uk/default.php">Bath Festival of Children's Literature</a>.  Later on in the week he will be further west in Appledore for their <a href="http://appledorebookfestival.co.uk/authorsandtickets.htm" rel="external" title="http://appledorebookfestival.co.uk/authorsandtickets.htm">book festival</a>.  On Thursday 1st October 2009, from 7.00pm he will be at St. Mary&rsquo;s Primary School (&pound;3).  His show is well worth seeing and you usually can buy his books there and get yours signed.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-243" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Back to school</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Tuesday, 22 September 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/" rel="external" title="www.vampirates.co.uk"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></a></div>Justin Somper has written on twitter again.  If you are not a follower and would like to be see <a href="http://twitter.com/JustinSomper" rel="external" title="http://twitter.com/JustinSomper">http://twitter.com/JustinSomper</a><br />"Looking forward to returning to my old secondary school - St Albans School - for an event tomorrow."<br />I wish him the best as he will be remembering everything that happened when he was at school.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-242" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">International Talk Like A Pirate Day</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 19 September 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-pirates.php">Pirates</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="../../../pirate/phrases/phrases.html" rel="self" title="Phrases"><img class="imageStyle" alt="jolly roger" src="jollyroger.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></a></div>Ahoy there my hearties, it be talk like a pirate day today.  Is anyone else joining in?<br /><br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-241" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">International Talk Like A Pirate Day</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Thursday, 17 September 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-pirates.php">Pirates</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="../../../pirate/phrases/phrases.html" rel="self" title="Phrases"><img class="imageStyle" alt="jolly roger" src="jollyroger.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></a></div>Although International Talk Like A Pirate Day is Saturday, several companies, schools etc are being pirates tomorrow.  So to help you here are some <a href="../../../pirate/phrases/phrases.html" rel="self" title="Phrases">phrases</a> that might help you be a pirate too.<br /><br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-240" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Justin is in the Times</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Tuesday, 15 September 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/" rel="external" title="www.vampirates.co.uk"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></a></div>Another review of Demons of the Ocean but this time with comments about how reading can be seen as a chore to some and how stories can relate to life around us.<br />For the article please see <a href="http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/life_and_style/education/article6832169.ece" rel="external" title="www.timesonline.co.uk">www.timesonline.co.uk</a><br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-239" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">International Talk Like A Pirate Day</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Monday, 14 September 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-pirates.php">Pirates</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="../../../pirate/phrases/phrases.html" rel="self" title="Phrases"><img class="imageStyle" alt="jolly roger" src="jollyroger.jpg" width="40" height="39" /></a></div>Saturday 19th September is International Talk Like A Pirate Day (every year).  Please see <a href="http://talklikeapirate.com/about.html" rel="external" title="www.talklikeapirate.com">www.talklikeapirate.com</a>, <a href="http://www.wikihow.com/Talk-Like-a-Pirate" rel="external" title="www.wikihow.com/Talk-Like-a-Pirate">http://www.wikihow.com/Talk-Like-a-Pirate</a> and <a href="http://www.yarr.org.uk/talk/" rel="external" title="www.yarr.org.uk">www.yarr.org.uk/talk</a> for more information.  I have listed out some <a href="../../../pirate/phrases/phrases.html" rel="self" title="Phrases">phrases</a> that might help under our pirates section.  You are welcome to write a post for this blog in pirate talk, just send it via the squeak page.  Being land locked at the moment, my son has even found a song for us, go and read the <a href="../../../pirate/song/song.html" rel="self" title="Song Lyrics">Last Saskatchewan Pirate Lyrics</a>.  His <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4qtX2qy4wug" rel="external" title="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4qtX2qy4wug">school</a>'s nick name is the pirates and so are celebrating it on the Friday.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-234" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Appologies</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 12 September 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-tempesttwins.php">TempestTwins</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="mouse" src="mouse.jpg" width="41" height="41" /></div>Appologies for the delay in publishing the updates it did not go up first time.  I was working on the error that is causing the blog to hang each time.  I discovered that when my husband upgraded his operating software on his machine from Leopard to Snow Leopard the software (Rapid Weaver) could not cope with the change.  The delay was caused by getting an old version of Rapid Weaver to work on a different machine (the one that crashed at Christmas) using Tiger operating system.  But if you can read this everything should be back to normal.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-235" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Mountains to the Sea Book Festival - Update</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Tuesday, 08 September 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/" rel="external" title="www.vampirates.co.uk"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></a></div>From Justin Somper on Twitter.<br />Howdy, Friday's event is for invited schools only. The public event is on Saturday 12th @ 2:30 pm. Hope that clears things up for you!<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-236" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Mountains to the Sea Book Festival in Dun Laoghaire, Dublin</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 05 September 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/" rel="external" title="www.vampirates.co.uk"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></a></div>I have found Vampirates stop press has more information on the Mountains to the Sea Book Festival in Dun Laoghaire, Dublin.<br />Please see <a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/stop-press/seejustinindublinandlondon/" rel="external" title="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/stop-press/seejustinindublinandlondon/">www.vampirates.co.uk/stop-press</a><br /><br />Tickets are now available for the <a href="http://www.mountainstosea.ie" rel="external" title="http://www.mountainstosea.ie">Mountains to the Sea Book Festival</a> in Dun Laoghaire 10-13 September 2009 with<br />Meet Justin Somper author of The Vampirates series at 10am at Hughes & Hughes, Marine Rd, Dun Laoghaire (Free)<br /><br />Acording to <a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/stop-press/seejustinindublinandlondon/" rel="external" title="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/stop-press/seejustinindublinandlondon/">www.vampirates.co.uk/stop-press</a> it is Saturday 12 September 2009 and according to <a href="http://www.mountainstosea.ie" rel="external" title="http://www.mountainstosea.ie">Mountains to the Sea Book Festival</a> it is Friday 11 September.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-237" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Cheltenham Literature Festival</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Friday, 04 September 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="http://cheltenhamfestivals.com/literature/" rel="external" title="http://cheltenhamfestivals.com/literature/"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></a></div>I have found an article on the festival - Book it!<br />Please see <a href="http://www.booktrade.info/index.php/showarticle/23098" rel="external" title="http://www.booktrade.info/index.php/showarticle/23098">www.booktrade.info/index.php/showarticle/23098</a><br /><br />Tickets are now on sale for the <a href="http://cheltenhamfestivals.com/literature/" rel="external" title="http://cheltenhamfestivals.com/literature/">Times Cheltenham Literature Festival</a> 9-18 October 2009 with<br />Breaking the Rules: Vampires vs Werewolves: Justin Somper & Maggie Stiefvater on Saturday 17 October 2009 at 5:15 pm (60mins)<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-232" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Twitter</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Tuesday, 01 September 2009 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span><span class="blog-entry-category"> <a href="category-books.php">Books</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="http://www.freewebs.com/thenocturn/index.htm" rel="external" title="The Nocturn"><img class="imageStyle" alt="ship" src="ship.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></a></div><br />For anyone on Twitter you can now follow the official TheNocturn twitter profile.  So you can catch up on news from <br /><a href="http://twitter.com/thenocturn" rel="external" title="http://twitter.com/thenocturn">twitter.com/thenocturn</a><br /><a href="http://twitter.com/JustinSomper" rel="external" title="http://twitter.com/JustinSomper">twitter.com/JustinSomper</a><br /><a href="http://www.freewebs.com/thenocturn/index.htm" rel="external" title="The Nocturn">www.freewebs.com/thenocturn/index.htm</a><br />and never forget <a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk" rel="external" title="http://www.vampirates.co.uk">www.vampirates.co.uk</a><br /></div></div>
	</div>
	
	 
